column11: Q1

This survey is being conducted by students in GS 102 for a class assignment. It should only take you 3 minutes to complete. Your participation is voluntary and your responses are anonymous to ensure your privacy. You are free to decline to answer any questions. The survey explores whether and/or in what ways environmental considerations shape the decisions Cal undergrads make. While there is no direct benefit to you as a participant, the results from the study may help us understand how environmental issues shape your everyday choices (actions, purchases, recycling...) By consenting to participate in this survey, you are verifying that you are currently a UC Berkeley undergraduate and that you are voluntarily agreeing to partake in this research. If you have any questions about this study, you can send an email to paget@berkeley.edu. Thank you !
column12: My time at UC Berkeley has increased my awareness about making environmentally conscious decisions.
column13: UC Berkeley’s infrastructure and services contribute to students’ ability to make environmentally conscious decisions.
column14: I am involved in organizations/clubs that contribute to combating climate change.
column15: I take climate change into consideration when making everyday purchasing decisions.
column16: I take public transportation because I want to reduce my ecological footprint.
column17: My food consumption reflects my desire to reduce my ecological footprint.
column18: I recycle/compost because I want to reduce my ecological footprint.
column19: My socioeconomic status has a significant impact on my environmental considerations.
column20: Choosing a career that in some way works to combat climate change is a top priority for me.
column22: In which program is your primary major located?
column24: Which race / ethnicity do you identify with the most? *(We understand these options are limited, but we are using this to compare to UC Berkeley’s Demographics.)
column26: What U.S. political party do you most identify with?
